00:19:31,396 --> 00:19:37,820
We can have a guaranteed quitter when that rate quit when that skill gap gets up in the 400 range.

386
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:45,106
So again this tells us here that as the team skill gap increases the chance of players quitting out

387
00:19:45,106 --> 00:19:48,408
is going up very quickly and it's very important to our players.

388
00:19:49,578 --> 00:19:53,479
So the takeaway here is, yes, the team gap is important,

389
00:19:53,479 --> 00:19:55,780
even more important in some ways than the personal gap.

390
00:19:55,780 --> 00:19:58,041
It will lead to more quits.

391
00:19:58,041 --> 00:20:02,022
And we can use that graph again to tune which team graphs,

392
00:20:02,022 --> 00:20:05,642
team gaps are appropriate for our players.

