00:33:27,391 --> 00:33:29,252
and the fact that they lost isn't as big of a deal.

671
00:33:29,252 --> 00:33:31,253
So it turns out, at least for Halo 5,

672
00:33:31,253 --> 00:33:33,995
what our players really seem to care about

673
00:33:33,995 --> 00:33:36,316
is that team skill gap, which is

674
00:33:36,910 --> 00:33:38,731
Do I have a shot at winning this match?

675
00:33:38,731 --> 00:33:39,772
And the personal skill gap, which is,

676
00:33:39,772 --> 00:33:42,954
if I come around the corner and I see an enemy,

677
00:33:42,954 --> 00:33:44,795
what will my success rate be in that encounter?

678
00:33:44,795 --> 00:33:47,017
Can I experience the gameplay?

679
00:33:47,017 --> 00:33:49,418
The other aspects that are commonly thought of

