00:35:56,085 --> 00:35:58,826
And the reason kind of why it can't be used

734
00:35:58,826 --> 00:36:02,688
goes into some pretty complicated reasons.

735
00:36:02,688 --> 00:36:05,009
I can't cover all of them in one slide,

736
00:36:05,009 --> 00:36:08,470
but some research that Microsoft Research did

737
00:36:08,470 --> 00:36:11,812
showed that the optimal skill gap to matchmake on,

738
00:36:11,812 --> 00:36:15,634
for example, depends on the population itself

739
00:36:15,634 --> 00:36:17,134
at the time you're matchmaking.

740
00:36:17,134 --> 00:36:20,536
The problem is an A-B test will split that population.

741
00:36:21,057 --> 00:36:26,263
So what you will learn from that A-B test is what is optimal for the way you've split,

742
00:36:26,263 --> 00:36:32,710
but that split may not be what the merged population is like. So you can't really do

743
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:37,796
that. You're learning the wrong optimal settings for the wrong population. So what you can do

744
00:36:37,796 --> 00:36:41,120
instead, and what we're looking forward to trying at some point, is

745
00:36:42,178 --> 00:36:45,120
what you do is you flip a coin every hour

746
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:47,301
and choose every time you flip that coin

747
00:36:47,301 --> 00:36:48,422
whether to go with A or B.

748
00:36:48,422 --> 00:36:49,682
And where A is like,

749
00:36:49,682 --> 00:36:51,283
A is how we're matchmaking right now

750
00:36:51,283 --> 00:36:52,804
and B is the new thing we want to try.

751
00:36:52,804 --> 00:36:54,085
You flip the coin

752
00:36:54,085 --> 00:36:56,026
because you need to have some randomness.

753
00:36:56,026 --> 00:36:58,208
You don't want to have like the time of day

754
00:36:58,208 --> 00:37:00,989
be messing up, causing correlations in this data.

755
00:37:00,989 --> 00:37:02,610
So you just flip that coin

756
00:37:02,610 --> 00:37:04,091
over an extended period of time, every hour,

757
00:37:04,091 --> 00:37:06,252
and you flip back and forth between these methods

758
00:37:06,252 --> 00:37:08,774
and watch how the players react during those methods

759
00:37:08,774 --> 00:37:10,835
and then check your metrics between those

760
00:37:11,644 --> 00:37:14,525
A and B the same way you would for any other A-B test.

761
00:37:14,525 --> 00:37:19,068
That way you are measuring on the correct population.

762
